                </provenance>
                  <provenance> A signature on both sides (upside down and very
                     faded on the recto) ‘<persName role="signer" key="person_2545">Wyllyam Brereton</persName>’; also on the verso ‘<persName role="signer" key="person_2543">Iame tayler</persName>’ and ‘<persName role="signer" key="person_2541">Anne
                Bere</persName>’. The first may be one of the several Cheshire men of the name active in the
                early sixteenth century, e.g. Sir William of Brereton Green, who died as Lord
                Justice of Ireland in 1541.</provenance>
